When [Insights](../insights/insights) is used with an On-premise hosted setup, any custom headers that include UPPERCASE letters or underscores (\_) will have these characters converted to lowercase letters and hyphens (-).&#x20;

**Examples:**&#x20;

```json
curl -i -X POST \
   -H "Content-Type:application/json" \
   -H "Custom_Header_1:value1" \ //Custom header with _ and UPPERCASE
   -H "Custom_Header_2:0123456789" \
   -d \
'{}' \
 ''
